Y16 isVowel

Given a character 'S' verify either it is Vowel or Consonant.

Input Format

Single character represents Alphabet 'S'.

Constraints

All the characters belongs to Alphabets.

Output Format

Print Vowel if the given character is vowel, Print Consonant if it is Consonant.

Sample Input 0

A
Sample Output 0

Vowel
Sample Input 1

b
Sample Output 1

Consonant

Solution:

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner ik=new Scanner(System.in);
          char c=ik.next().charAt(0);
        if(c=='a' || c=='e' || c=='i' || c=='o'|| c=='u')
        {
            System.out.println("Vowel");
        }
        else if (c=='A' || c=='E' || c=='I' || c=='O' || c=='U')
        {
              System.out.println("Vowel");
        }
        else
        {
              System.out.println("Consonant");
        }
            
    }
}
